title: All great
text: Great location, great sleep quality, decoration, all a great experience. The breakfast was also worth mentioning, many options to chose from and I bet there are locals visiting it only for the breakfast hehehe, no way we were that many on the hotel.

title: Small museum
text: Not much to see here, a large room and a smaller one on the basement. Your experience will depend on the exhibit they have at the time.
place: MUCA Museum of Urban and Contemporary Art

title: High expectations
text: I wanted to go there for a few years, but it was just not a good museum, the collections were not chronological and there was a feeling of discontinuing the path overall. Probably got spoiled from the Mercedes Benz museum which did a better experience

title: Try the rice
text: The aromatic rice was something worth trying by itself, the dumpling were so so, but good. I would for sure go back

title: Great price, good product
text: Great price, good product but it depends really on what you add inside. I ordered a plate with one of each and inthe chicken ones where the best by far. They are cooked in the spot.

title: Great value
text: Not expensive, large rooms and no complains. The location is not downtown but it’s not so far to strike it out. They have breakfast as an add on option. Price is the main driver here, but the place comes as a good surprise.

title: Quality ingredients. The place
text: Quality ingredients. The place is cosy and local, so no menus in English and such, but also you don’t need much information for the few items in the menu. Very good taste.

title: Good price, great taste
text: Good price, great taste and kind service. I thought the portions were small but it was the presentation only, in reality they are very fulfilling. I would come back.

title: Some views
text: The main close up view is directly from the Punkva caves on the bottom, and I think you need reservations for that, not from the viewing platforms. The top and middle views are easily reachable with steps.

title: Classy
text: Design, space and good taste, the price is not in the low range but well worth it, it’s just comfy and big. Breakfast was included and it was good enough, warm offerings and some classic bread options. I really liked it.

title: Need your own wheels
text:
Not an easy destination. You will need your own wheels and even with that, there is not space next to the road to park usually, or space at all for kilometers, so your best bet for a photo safari will be to take a bike. But where exactly? Information on internet is vague and mentions 7 towns.

Most of the good views are in one small road around 48°58'20.5"N 17°03'05.5"E . Still, no place to park just quick stops on the widening of the road to overtake and there is local traffic, so it’s not a deserted road. It’s a little let down, it’s not really prepared for tourism and probably leaving that coordinate above will make more people go, but so be it. Probably also will help eventually adding some more view points along the route.

Also you know most of the good photos have photoshop right? The place is there and under the right light will look like the photo, but it’s nature, so it does what it does.

title: Just like the photos
text: Friendly staff, great rooms and perfect location. Not parking friendly but the P1 parking is just 7 minutes walking. They sell day parking tickets for 11 euros so it’s cheaper than paying per hour. We couldn’t try the breakfast but coffee was free

title: Cute
text: Charming houses all the way to the castle main entrance. Go this way and not via the parking lot, it’s a manicured street where all is photo worthy

title: Does it job as breakfast place.
text: Does it job as breakfast place. Serves food and has views and that’s it. Food was not particularly good or bad, but it’s still recomendable even if it’s only for the terrace

title: Better from afar
text: The place itself it’s good, but the best way to see it it’s not on it, but looking it from the city. Loved it.

title: The highlight
text: The best views and the most interesting buildings are in the castle area, worth to climb to the tower and spend the 20 minutes museum walk. Quite a hen this place.

title: Charming
text: Picture perfect town where you can’t get lost, probably takes 2 hours literally to walk every street of the tourist areas, but there are many inviting places to sit and sip a beer.

title: Good taste and perfect location,
text: Good taste and perfect location, family owned, even if it’s huge, my only complain is that the sandwich didn’t look like the one on the photo but the taste was good.

title: Brutal castle
text: Not the usual delicate and sweet castle, a strong exemplar of architecture with good walks and an eye candy structure. Good stop for a maybe 1 hour.

title: Small
text: Some charm and unique character by being divided by 3 rivers, but otherwise it would be just like any other town. Still the 3 rivers thing make it worthy of visit.

title: Landmark
text: Most of the thing to see here it’s already on the photos of the place. Good photo subject and a malecón walk around it

title: Ceilings
text: Under renovation just you can still see the ceiling and the detail on them, not only a big building but also with some interesting paintings.

title: Just the name
text: No art around just some small alley to walk around with a few cafes. Nothing remarkable, mostly an alley with a fancy name.

title: Merging rivers
text: First time seeing 2 different color rivers merge. I wasn’t even really sure if rivers were really a different color before or if it’s just the light and stones, but here you can see a dark brown and a greenish river merge. Worth the stop for sure.

title: Delicious. I didn’t expect
text: Delicious. I didn’t expect much, just wanted to eat but the food was just great. Even the house beer was note worthy. Very good place indeed.

title: Less than a minute stop
text: More funny or curios than interesting, a big head in a random corner it’s a good photo op, but nothing else.

title: Not bad, but not the best
text: Not bad, but not the best of the world neither. Service is quick and friendly, they accept only cash and the convertion rate is quite high if paying with euros.

title: Does the job.
text: Not really for the masses of tourism, mostly there to serve the seasonal workers but it does its job. Clean enough and weirdly in the middle of nothing hehehe. It has self check in which is practical.

title: Unexpected
text: 10 EUR entrance but really worth it. Specter something small and kitsch but it was a real surprise, you can see some details v/well worked.

title: Memorable. Good ice. It’s
text: Memorable. Good ice. It’s crowded and seems to be very popular, definitely a place un would come back to visit again

title: Heart of the city
text: Everything happens here not far from here. The main attraction of the city for some reason. Better during the summer months.

title: Great fish, quiet and nice place
text: Great fish, quiet and nice place and decent prices. A little out of the way from the main tourist hotspots.

title: Good was average, not bad
text: Good was average, not bad but not special. The resultant has indoors, street and garden space, would be worth it to take a look at the garden. Seems that they don’t have enough waiters but eventually you will get served.

title: Good entries
text:
The curry shrimp soup and the Morning Glory was delicious. The main dishes are bigger than in the usual Thai, maybe they are meant to be shared but also 50% more expensive.

Overall ok but I would ask what else they have besides the dishes on the menu, sometimes they have specials.

title: Favorite restaurant in Nuremberg
text: Favorite restaurant in Nuremberg, not only the food, it’s the vibe on the terrace and the fact that they have parking. Always a good choice.

title: Worth more time
text: I was planning to go there, make a few photos and drive out, but the park is really something worth spending a couple of hours in, it has a good vibe that makes you want to have a nap under the sun or drink a beer in the terrace

title: Fun
text: Great good looking castle, good vibe overall around it and don’t miss the park, it’s worth a couple of hours.

title: View from the top of the viewing tower
text: Many steps but good views of the maze from the top of the tower. Some nuclear towers and a wind farm can be seen in the distance too. No other highlights in the area.

title: One of 300 in Germany
text: One of the many Bismarck towers built around Germany, I didn’t find anything remarkable but it’s also one of the few attractions around. Probably enjoyed more looking at dead trees than this one.

title: Good
text: They forgot to add towels in our room but well, that happens. Lively bar downstairs and big spacious room, modern decoration and overall good sleep quality. The whole state is not COVID scared and the hotel has the same mentality, so no masks needed and such, even if you are getting people from all over Germany to stay over.

title: Perfect
text: The place has everything you need, bbq area a pool and many sitting space to enjoy an afternoon under the shade of the huge trees. Rooms are ok too, but this place is perfect for its garden, maybe it will be a completely difference experience on winter, but otherwise highly recommended, loved it.

title: Work in progress
text: Avoid it, it’s under repairs and there is not much to see besides it. Huge parking space, it will take one more year till it’s ready

title: Good deal
text: They take you through some of the less busy canals on the west for the 2 hours trip, had to wait a bit till the boat got full, but it was all good.

title: So so
text: An Asian restaurant, some interesting flavors but not remarkable. I didnt find much difference with other restaurants

title: Photogenic
text: No town around, just a couple of parking lots around. Many good views and points to see the bridge, probably an hour will do there.

title: Famous
text: Apparently it’s a famous statue and I noticed that it’s in the road shields from Thuringia. But it’s an statue and that’s pretty average. A famous one yes, but a very generic statue.

title: Free and interesting
text: No excuse not to go, it’s a good photo opp and a great way to spend 45 mins. I am glad we did made the small detour there

title: We had only one soup and a
text: We had only one soup and a beer, but that was a very good soup, some new way at least for me to do a lentils with cumin and korkuma. I will look to steal the idea.

title: Good ice cream, nice consistency
text: Good ice cream, nice consistency and flavor, decent prices. Not top notch ice cream but good for the price.

title: Classic place, good location
text: Classic place, good location and good for big groups specially in summer. As the name suggest all the beers are Augustiner.

title: Very big place
text: It was a perfect place to be with friends. We booked it for the weekend and even thou we didn’t fill the house they changed us per person which was fair. They have the implements for cooking and WiFi. It was a good choice to stay there. As expected, furniture is on the classical side of things.

title: Cool loop on the top
text: The small hike on the top is worth it, other people says it’s expensive but I remember more the experience than the price to be honest. Very good experience would recommend it

title: Big bar with music
text: Big bar with English music and good ambiance. They have a terrace and bbq food and some finger food when it’s too late

title: Cute
text: Big and lonely in a middle of a field, that’s a place that must be seen. I liked the road there by car, seeing the chapel between the trees as you approach

title: Clean and tidy
text: Good place, maybe a little on the middle top tier of the price range. Good location, big room, and some small details with good taste. Breakfast was included but it was mostly packaged jams and products with a few add ons that make it ok

title: Delicious
text: The usual dishes, but at least the mushroom plates with schnitzel and another one with Kloss where delicious, very very good. Fries were good too and you can see the hand of the chef with that.

title: Skeletons
text: The church is great itself, the the dozen of jeweled skeletons just make it perfect, so many things to see. Visit the Kappl too is not far and it’s pretty at least from the outside.

title: Great for kids
text: It all depends on the expectations I guess, and the word labyrinth is the cause. It’s more like a path with ways between very big rocks which was adequate by human work. Entertaining for a couple of hours with some minimal exercise needed

title: Classy
text: Good looking place and area. Classy. The food is not up to the price, while there is good dishes, there is no flavor out of the normal and pretty much you are paying for the location since other restaurants offer the same taste for less.

title: Local food.
text: One of the fue places with real “Monterrey” food. The menu is a good example of the different influences on the region diet. Not cheap, but worth it. Can be used too as a bar.
